// When the async-await scheduler runs this on a green thread (AsyncTrace builds),
// it brackets the underlying I/O with `io_yield #<id> [file_exists]` /
// `io_resume #<id> [file_exists]` trace lines, matching the spec's expected
// scheduling trace. `__gt_current_trace_id` returns 0 off a green thread, so the
// guards skip the trace on the main thread and in non-async code; `__gt_trace_emit`
// additionally self-gates on the runtime trace flag, so a normal build is silent.
//
// Slot usage: slot 0 = path *, slot 1 = GT trace id (0 if not on a GT),
//             slot 2 = mrt_file_exists_impl result.
